\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ntests/test_operator_assembly_modes.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ntests/test_operator_contract.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ntests/test_operator_qa.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ntests/test_registry.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ntests/test_selection.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ntests/test_surface_operators.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-006_Run_a_Milestone_6_implementation_verification_pass_and_publish_a_readiness_report/stdout.jsonl:18:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_6\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' docs/operator_qa.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Offline Operator QA Workflow\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 6 is not finished when bundles merely serialize. Before Milestone 10\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nstarts, the team needs one offline workflow that can:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- initialize a localized pulse on the fine surface\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- check that a lightweight smoke evolution behaves stably enough for pre-engine work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- compare fine and coarse behavior quantitatively\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- show the result on the mesh and patch decomposition without opening raw arrays\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`scripts/06_operator_qa.py` is that workflow.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Inputs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe report reads only local bundle artifacts that were already built by\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py`:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_fine_operator.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_coarse_operator.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_transfer_operators.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_operator_metadata.json`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- optional descriptor / geometry-QA sidecars for extra context\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nNo FlyWire token or network access is required.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Run It\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nInspect one or more explicit root IDs:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npython scripts/06_operator_qa.py --config config/local.yaml --root-id 101 --root-id 102\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nInspect the active selected subset:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npython scripts/06_operator_qa.py --config config/local.yaml --limit 4\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nEquivalent Make target:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nmake operator-qa CONFIG=config/local.yaml\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nOptional smoke depth override:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```bash\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\npython scripts/06_operator_qa.py --config config/local.yaml --root-id 101 --pulse-steps 12\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Output Layout\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe output directory is deterministic for the exact sorted root-id set:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nconfig.paths.operator_qa_dir/root-ids-<sorted-root-ids>/\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nExample:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```text\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/index.html\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/report.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/summary.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_details.json\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_pulse_initial.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_boundary_mask.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_patch_decomposition.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_fine_pulse_final.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_coarse_pulse_final.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_coarse_reconstruction.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndata/processed/operator_qa/root-ids-101/101_reconstruction_error.svg\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThat path stability is deliberate so the report can be referenced from run logs,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nticket notes, or review comments.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## What It Checks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe current report combines bundle-level structural checks with one\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nstability-oriented pulse smoke loop.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nStructural checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fine and coarse operator symmetry residuals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fine and coarse constant-field nullspace residuals on the stiffness matrices\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- non-positive mass counts on fine and coarse mass diagonals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- coarse-versus-fine Galerkin and application residuals already serialized in\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  the transfer bundle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPulse smoke checks:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- deterministic localized pulse initialization from the fine bundle’s stored\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  geodesic neighborhood data\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- explicit diffusion-style stepping with `dt` derived from the estimated\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  largest eigenvalue of the symmetric mass-normalized operator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- mass drift across the smoke evolution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- Dirichlet-energy monotonicity under the chosen time step\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- final coarse-vs-restricted-fine residual\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- final fine-vs-prolongated-coarse residual\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe report also renders:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- pulse initialization on the fine surface\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- boundary-mask inspection\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- patch decomposition\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fine pulse after the smoke loop\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- coarse pulse after the smoke loop\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- prolongated coarse reconstruction on the fine surface\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- absolute reconstruction error on the fine surface\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Gate Semantics\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nEvery metric gets `pass`, `warn`, or `fail`. The aggregate report also emits a\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 10 gate:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `go`: no warnings or failures\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `review`: no blocking failures, but at least one warning or non-blocking failure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `hold`: at least one blocking failure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nUse that gate this way:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `go`: acceptable baseline for downstream engine integration and solver work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `review`: engine work can continue only if a reviewer signs off on the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  degraded metrics and the visual overlays still look scientifically plausible\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `hold`: do not treat the operator bundle as an engine baseline; rebuild or\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  debug the bundle first\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Reviewer Checklist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nReviewers should look for:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- pulse initialization staying localized around one seed region rather than\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  starting already smeared across the whole surface\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- boundary masks matching the intended surface topology instead of lighting up\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  unexpected interior structure\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fine smoke evolution diffusing smoothly without explosive growth or obvious\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  checkerboard artifacts\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- coarse pulse support following the same broad region as the restricted fine\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  result\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- prolongated coarse reconstruction tracking the fine field instead of\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  collapsing onto a few dominant patches\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- reconstruction error concentrating near coarse partition limits rather than\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  covering the whole neuron\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nWhen the report fails:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- if symmetry, nullspace, or non-positive-mass checks fail, stop Milestone 10\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  work and inspect the operator build itself\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- if pulse mass or energy checks fail, treat the bundle as numerically unstable\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  for pre-engine use\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- if only coarse-vs-fine comparison checks warn or fail, inspect the patch\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  decomposition and transfer quality before deciding whether the bundle is still\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  usable for exploratory work\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Threshold Overrides\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nOptional overrides live under `meshing.operator_qa_thresholds` in the config and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfollow the same shape as the geometry-QA thresholds:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```yaml\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nmeshing:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  operator_qa_thresholds:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n    pulse_final_fine_vs_prolongated_coarse_residual_relative:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      warn: 0.25\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      fail: 0.60\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n      blocking: false\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nTighten thresholds when using the workflow as a release gate. Relax them only\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nwhen the report is being used for exploratory analysis and the deviation is\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndocumented explicitly.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T185349Z/FW-M6-006_Run_a_Milestone_6_implementation_verification_pass_and_publish_a_readiness_report/stdout.jsonl:42:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_20\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,240p' docs/pipeline_notes.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Pipeline notes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Recommended workflow\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. Use FlyWire Codex bulk exports for stable metadata snapshots.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. Use CAVE / fafbseg for programmatic per-neuron access.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. Build local preprocessed assets so the simulator does not talk to FlyWire live during runtime.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Why this repo uses selective meshing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe female whole brain is the structural scaffold, but the final simulation should only keep a small subset in a mesh-wave state at once. That matches a multiresolution strategy:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- whole brain mapped,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- selected circuit meshed,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- only active patches numerically updated.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Artifact contracts\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Subset-selection contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Geometry handoff contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_fine_operator.npz`: fine surface operator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_coarse_operator.npz`: Galerkin coarse patch operator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe processed graph archives intentionally separate fine and coarse data:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the surface graph stores the simplified mesh vertices/faces, sparse surface adjacency/Laplacian arrays, and `surface_to_patch` so every surface vertex has an explicit coarse patch assignment\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the fine operator archive stores cotangent stiffness and mass-normalized operator matrices plus explicit supporting geometry including edge lengths/weights, lumped mass, normals, tangent frames, boundary masks, anisotropy coefficients (`anisotropy_vertex_tensor_diagonal`, `anisotropy_edge_direction_uv`, `anisotropy_edge_multiplier`, `effective_cotangent_weights`), and capped edge-geodesic neighborhoods\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the patch graph stores sparse coarse adjacency/Laplacian arrays plus `patch_sizes`, `patch_centroids`, `patch_seed_vertices`, and CSR-style `member_vertex_indices` / `member_vertex_indptr` arrays for reconstructing patch membership deterministically\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the coarse operator archive stores patch mass / area, Galerkin-projected stiffness, the mass-normalized coarse operator, and the quality metrics used to compare coarse and fine application\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_transfer_operators.npz` stores explicit fine/coarse transfer structure, physical-field restriction / prolongation matrices, normalized-state transfer operators, and transfer-quality metrics\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_operator_metadata.json` records the realized discretization family, fallback mode, versioned `operator_assembly` config, boundary mode, anisotropy model, geodesic-neighborhood settings, transfer availability, coarse assembly rule, and coarse-versus-fine quality metrics for downstream discovery\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nmaterialization version, an explicit meshing-config snapshot including\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n`meshing.operator_assembly`, and per-root asset\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nstatuses/paths. Raw fetch runs also record `raw_asset_provenance` per\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nroot ID so cache hits, refetches, skips, validation failures, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\noptional skeleton fetch errors can be audited without reading console\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nlogs. Processed bundle records also expose `artifact_sources` so each\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nsimplified mesh, surface graph, patch graph, and sidecar points back to\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nthe raw mesh and skeleton inputs it was built against.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDescriptor and QA rationale:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `docs/geometry_descriptor_qa.md` documents the default `meshing.qa_thresholds`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  profile, what each descriptor bucket is meant to capture, and which failed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  checks should block downstream use by default.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCompatibility shim:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  sidecar name during migration.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `docs/operator_bundle_design.md` is the authoritative Milestone 6 operator\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  decision note; later tickets should cite it instead of re-litigating the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  default discretization family.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Offline operator QA contract\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 6 also now defines one deterministic offline inspection workflow for\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\noperator bundles:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `scripts/06_operator_qa.py` reads the local fine operator, coarse operator,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  transfer bundle, patch graph, and operator metadata for one or more root IDs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- output goes to `config.paths.operator_qa_dir/root-ids-<sorted-root-ids>/`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the report is static: `index.html`, `report.md`, `summary.json`,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  per-root detail JSON, and SVG panels for pulse initialization, boundary-mask\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  inspection, patch decomposition, smoke-evolved fine/coarse fields, and coarse\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  reconstruction error\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the report summary includes pass / warn / fail checks plus a Milestone 10\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  gate of `go`, `review`, or `hold`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nSee `docs/operator_qa.md` for the full reviewer checklist and gate semantics.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T222203Z/FW-M7-006_Run_a_Milestone_7_integration_verification_pass_and_publish_a_readiness_report/stdout.jsonl:18:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_7\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' docs/coupling_bundle_design.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"# Milestone 7 Synapse Asset Contract And Coupling Topology Choice\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThis note freezes the Milestone 7 synapse and inter-neuron coupling handoff so\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nlater simulator and UI work can target one explicit manifest contract, one\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nexplicit bundle layout, and one explicit coupling interpretation.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Contract summary\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe processed manifest now carries `_coupling_contract_version:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ncoupling_bundle.v1` plus a per-root `coupling_bundle` block.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe top-level contract owns:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the authoritative local synapse-registry path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the versioned design-note reference and design-note version\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the supported coupling-topology families\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the supported fallback modes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the default sign, delay, aggregation, and missing-geometry policies\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the canonical root-asset and edge-bundle directories\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nEach per-root `coupling_bundle` block owns:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the same contract and design-note versions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the realized topology family for that root-local handoff\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the fallback hierarchy the later mapping/assembly stages must follow\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the sign and delay representation rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the multi-synapse aggregation rule\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the discoverable local synapse registry pointer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the incoming and outgoing anchor-map artifact paths\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the root-local coupling index path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- any explicit edge-level coupling bundle references that already exist\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe canonical Milestone 7 layout is:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/synapse_registry.csv`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/roots/<root_id>_incoming_anchor_map.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/roots/<root_id>_outgoing_anchor_map.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/roots/<root_id>_coupling_index.json`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `config.paths.processed_coupling_dir/edges/<pre_root_id>__to__<post_root_id>_coupling.npz`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nLater tickets may add more sidecars, but those filenames and manifest fields are\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nthe stable discovery surface.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Candidate topology families\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Point-to-point\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDefinition:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- each synapse maps to one presynaptic readout anchor and one postsynaptic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  landing anchor\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the coupling artifact stays close to the raw synapse table\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAdvantages:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- highest localization fidelity\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- easy to inspect against raw synapse rows\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- minimal aggregation assumptions\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCosts:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- expensive to evaluate for dense edges\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- overly sensitive to mesh simplification or anchor jitter\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- awkward when a later solver runs on patches instead of vertices\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- does not naturally share one representation across surface, skeleton, and\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  point-neuron fallbacks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Patch-to-patch\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDefinition:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- each connectome edge becomes one or more direct transfers between coarse patch\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  IDs\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- synapse detail is collapsed early into patch-pair weights\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAdvantages:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- cheap to serialize and simulate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- easy to compare to coarse point-neuron baselines\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- naturally aligned with reduced patch-state models\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCosts:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- throws away within-patch landing structure too early\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- strongly depends on the current patch partition\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- makes later refinement back to finer resolution difficult\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- mixes geometric localization and aggregation into one irreversible step\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Distributed patch-cloud\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nDefinition:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- each synapse or aggregate contributes a sparse cloud over a small set of\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  presynaptic readout anchors and postsynaptic landing anchors\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- edge bundles may aggregate multiple synapses, but only after preserving the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  cloud structure that records where activity is sampled and where it lands\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nAdvantages:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- preserves locality without forcing the simulator to operate on one raw\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  synapse at a time\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- works with surface patches now and still degrades cleanly to skeleton or\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  point-neuron fallbacks\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- keeps the handoff compatible with both coarse and finer later solvers\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- separates geometry localization from sign, delay, and weight aggregation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCosts:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- more metadata than direct patch-to-patch coupling\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- requires an explicit normalization convention inside each cloud\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- needs careful testing so aggregation stays deterministic\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Decision\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe default Milestone 7 coupling topology is `distributed_patch_cloud`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nPoint-to-point and patch-to-patch remain recognized comparison families for\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ndebugging, ablations, or future coarse baselines, but the authoritative\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 7 handoff assumes that coupling is a sparse cloud-to-cloud transfer\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nderived from synapse-local anchors.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nWhy this is the default:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- it preserves enough geometry to justify morphology-resolved simulation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- it avoids binding the later solver to raw per-synapse loops\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- it keeps one contract usable across mixed morphology classes\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- it postpones irreversible aggregation until sign, delay, and fallback mode are\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  already explicit\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Fallback hierarchy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nLater mapping and coupling tickets must follow this hierarchy in order:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n1. `surface_patch_cloud`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n2. `skeleton_segment_cloud`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n3. `point_neuron_lumped`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMeaning:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `surface_patch_cloud`: default. Use surface/patch anchors from the Milestone 5\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  and 6 geometry/operator bundles.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `skeleton_segment_cloud`: fallback when surface geometry is missing or not\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  trusted but a usable skeleton anchor representation exists.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `point_neuron_lumped`: last resort when only a reduced single-state\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  representation is available.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCurrent anchor realization notes for the shipped Milestone 7 mapper:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- surface mode localizes to deterministic coarse patch anchors while also\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  recording the nearest supporting surface vertex and residuals\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- skeleton mode currently localizes to the nearest raw SWC node so the fallback\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  stays easy to audit before any later segment-parameter refinement\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- point mode uses one deterministic root-local lumped anchor proxy per\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  direction, derived from the mean available synapse query point for that root\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMissing geometry is never a silent drop. Every mapped synapse or aggregated edge\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nmust either:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- record the realized fallback mode explicitly, or\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- record a structured blocked reason explaining why no supported fallback was\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  possible\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Sign, delay, and aggregation rules\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Sign representation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 7 uses `categorical_sign_with_signed_weight`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThat means later bundles must carry both:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- an explicit semantic sign label such as excitatory, inhibitory, modulatory, or\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  unknown\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- a signed numeric coupling weight or gain term\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRules:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- unknown sign must stay explicit; it may not be silently coerced to positive\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- opposite signs may not be merged into one net scalar without preserving the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  polarity split\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- downstream consumers should read the categorical field first and treat the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  signed numeric field as the magnitude/polarity realization of that label\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Delay representation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 7 uses `nonnegative_delay_ms_per_synapse_or_delay_bin`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRules:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- delays are serialized in milliseconds\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- delays must be finite and non-negative\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- heterogeneous delays on one biological edge may be aggregated into bins, but\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  not collapsed to one mean value unless the bundle explicitly declares that\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  approximation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Kernel family and normalization\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 7 now ships one default kernel-family contract:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- kernel family: `separable_rank_one_cloud`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- source cloud normalization: `sum_to_one_per_component`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- target cloud normalization: `sum_to_one_per_component`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMeaning:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- each aggregate first samples a weighted presynaptic readout cloud\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the resulting event is then distributed over a weighted postsynaptic landing\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  cloud\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the scalar coupling gain stays in the aggregate's signed weight total rather\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  than being hidden inside the cloud weights\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nSupported explicit alternatives remain limited on purpose:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `point_impulse` is reserved for point-like bundles where each aggregate has\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  one source anchor and one target anchor\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `none` may be used for source or target cloud normalization when a later\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  consumer wants raw anchor-weight totals instead of unit-sum clouds\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Delay model\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 7 now ships one conservative default delay model:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- delay model: `constant_zero_ms`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nand one explicit geometric alternative:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `euclidean_anchor_distance_over_velocity`\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nThe bundle always records the chosen delay model plus its parameters\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n(`base_delay_ms`, `velocity_distance_units_per_ms`, and `delay_bin_size_ms`) so\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nlater baseline and wave simulators can share the same handoff even when they\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ninterpret the transfer physics differently.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n### Multi-synapse aggregation\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nMilestone 7 uses `sum_over_synapses_preserving_sign_and_delay_bins`.\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nRules:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- aggregate only after grouping by source root, target root, topology family,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  realized fallback mode, sign, delay bin, and kernel family\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- record at least the aggregated synapse count and total signed weight for each\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  aggregate\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- never cancel excitatory and inhibitory synapses into one unlabeled total\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- never merge distinct delay bins into one scalar without an explicit contracted\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  approximation field\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n## Invariants later milestones must preserve\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nLater simulator, mapping, and UI milestones should preserve these invariants\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\ninstead of silently changing them:\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- the local synapse registry is the auditable row-level source for every anchor\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  map and edge bundle\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- root-local anchor maps and edge bundles refer to the same root IDs and the\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  same design-note version recorded in the manifest\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- `distributed_patch_cloud` remains the default authoritative family unless a\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  later contract revision explicitly supersedes this one\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- fallback mode is an explicit data field, not an inference from missing arrays\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n- a bundle that distributes one coupling event over multiple anchors must state\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n  its normalization convention explicitly in the bundle metadata\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"exit_code\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":0,\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"}}\\\\\\\\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T222203Z/FW-M7-006_Run_a_Milestone_7_integration_verification_pass_and_publish_a_readiness_report/stdout.jsonl:30:{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item.completed\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"item_14\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command_execution\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"command\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' src/flywire_wave/coupling_contract.py\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"aggregated_output\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"from __future__ import annotations\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport copy\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nimport math\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom collections.abc import Mapping, Sequence\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nfrom typing import Any\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCOUPLING_BUNDLE_CONTRACT_VERSION = \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"coupling_bundle.v1\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\nCOUPLING_BUNDLE_DESIGN_NOTE = \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"docs/coupling_bundle_design.md\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\